<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,324,885,911]" box="[189,324,885,911]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,885,911]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,885,911]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[189,1398,932,994]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[641,751,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipilis">
<emphasis box="[641,751,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">brevipilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘short-haired’ and referring to the unusually short pile on the male cercus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
