<paragraph blockId="54.[189,1399,316,420]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
The sclerite between the bases of surstyli and posteriorly from the cerci is an unusual structure which 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,608,355,381]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipilis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[189,608,355,381]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) brevipilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[619,714,355,381]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares with only one other species known to us, 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plautus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">S (A.) plautus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[283,373,394,420]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
For more discussion, see under the latter.
</paragraph>
